The genealogy of Jesus
This is the genealogy of Jesus Christ: Jesus came from the line of David, and David from the line of Abraham.
Ibrahim is the father of Isaac. Isaac is the father of Jacob. Jacob is the father of Judah and his brothers.
Judah, father of Pharez and Zerah, whose mother was Tamar. Pharez was the father of Hezron. Hezron was the father of Aram.
Aram son of Abiur. Abiur son of Nachshon. Nachshon son of Salmon.
Salmon son of Boaz, whose mother was Rahab. Boaz son of Obed, whose mother was Rachele. Obed son of Jesse.
Jesse was David's father. David was the father of Solomon, whose mother was the wife of Uriah.
Sulaiman Abu Rahb'abam. Rahb'abam Abu Abiya. Abiya Abu Asa.
Asa, father of Joash. Joash, father of Uzziah. Uzziah, father of Jotham.
Aziz Abu Yutham. Yutham Abu Achaaz. Achaaz Abu Hezekiah.
Zachariah Abū Mansi. Mansi Abū Āmūn. Āmūn Abū Yohanan.
Josiah Abijam, #Abijam. 11:1 A different name for Hezekiah. His brothers. This until the exile of the children of Israel to Babylon.
After the exile to Babylon: Jekinai was the father of Shaltiel. Shaltiel was the father of Zerubbabel.
Zarbabal is father of Abi'Udhud. Abi'Udhud is father of Aliyakim. Aliyakim is father of 'Azor.
Azawr ibn Saaduq. Saaduq ibn Akhaim. Akhaim ibn Aliud.
Alyud ibn Al-Aziz. Al-Aziz ibn Mutan. Mutan ibn Yaqub.
Jacob Abu Yusuf, Mary's husband. And Mary is the mother of Jesus, who is called 'the Christ.'
There are fourteen generations from Abraham to David, fourteen from David to the exile, and fourteen from the exile to Christ. The birth of Jesus Christ
As for the birth of Jesus Christ, it took place as follows: His mother, Mary, was engaged to a man named Joseph. But before they were married, she became pregnant by the power of the Holy Spirit.
But Joseph found her to be a good woman, and he did not wish to reveal her secret, so he decided to leave her in peace.
While Joseph was thinking about this, an angel appeared to him in a dream and said to him: "Joseph, son of David, do not be afraid to take Mary as your wife, for the child she carries is of the Holy Spirit."
And she will bear a son, and you shall call his name Jesus, for he will save his people from their sins."
This happened so that what the Lord said through the Prophet might be fulfilled:
"Behold, the virgin will conceive and bear a son, and his name will be Emmanuel, which means 'God with us.'"
And when Joseph woke up from his sleep, he did everything as commanded by the angel of the Lord, and took his wife to his house.
But he did not know her until the child whom he named 'Jesus' was born.
Wise men from the East
And when Jesus was born in Bethlehem in the region of Judea during the reign of King Herod, some wise men from the East came to Jerusalem,
And they asked, "Where is the child who has been born recently, who is to be the king of the Jews? For we have seen his star in the east, and have come to worship him."
The king Herod was disturbed when he heard this, as were all the inhabitants of Jerusalem.
Herod gathered all the chief priests and scribes, and asked them where the Messiah was born.
They said to him: "In the city of Bethlehem in the region of Judea, for this is written by the prophet:"
«You, Bethlehem of Judea, are not insignificant among the rulers of Judah, for from you a ruler will come who will shepherd My people, Israel.»
And Herod called the scribes and the experts, and he honored them, and they informed him precisely of the time when the star appeared.
Then they sent them to the city of Bethlehem and said: "Go and look for the child. And when you find him, tell me, so that I too may go and prostrate myself before him."
So the wise men listened to the king and then departed. And behold, the star they had seen in the east was moving ahead of them until it reached and stood above the place where the child was.
Be exceedingly joyful when they saw the star.
They entered the house and saw the child with Mary his mother, and they prostrated themselves on the ground, worshipping him. Then they opened the chests containing their treasures and offered him gifts: gold, incense, and myrrh.
Then God warned them in a dream not to return to Herod, so they traveled to their homeland by another route. The flight to Egypt
And when the wise men had traveled, an angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream and said to him: "Rise, take the child and his mother and flee to Egypt, and remain there until I tell you, for Herod will search for the child to destroy him."
Then Joseph rose, took the child and his mother at night, and went to Egypt.
And this continued until Herod's death. This happened to fulfill what the Lord said through the prophet: "I have called my son from Egypt." #From... my son. 15:2 From the book of Hosea 11:1. Herod kills the children of Bethlehem
When Herod learned that the wise men had deceived him, he became extremely angry and ordered the killing of all children in Bethlehem and its surrounding area who were two years of age or younger, according to the time the wise men had told him.
At that time, what was said on the lips of the Prophet Jeremiah:
"A voice was heard in Ramah—a loud cry of Noach. It was Rachel weeping for her children, refusing to mourn because they were dead." Return from Egypt
After the death of Herod, an angel of the Lord appeared in a dream to Joseph in Egypt.
He said to him: "Get up, take the child and his mother, and return to the land of Israel, because those who tried to kill the child are dead."
Then Joseph rose, took the child and his mother, and went to the land of Israel.
But when he heard that Archelaus had become king in the region of Judea instead of his father Herod, he feared to go there. After God warned him in a dream, he went to the region of Galilee.
And he lived in a town called Nazareth. This event fulfilled the prophets' statement that the Messiah would be called a Nazarene. #Nazarene. 23:2 Named after the city of Nazareth. Also, it is a word similar to the Hebrew word meaning "branch," mentioned in Isaiah 11:1, pointing to the promise of the Messiah coming from the line of David.
John the Baptist
At that time John the Baptist came to preach in the Judean wilderness,
And he said: "Repent, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand."
And John says this is the one about whom the prophet Isaiah spoke when he said: "A voice of one man crying in the wilderness, saying: 'Make the way ready for the Lord. Straighten out the path for him.'"
John was dressed in garments made of camel's hair, and a belt of leather around his waist; and he ate locusts and wild honey.
At that time, people began coming from Jerusalem and from all of the Jewish region, and from the area around the Jordan River, to hear him.
And he would lead them to the Jordan River after they had confessed their sins.
And when John saw that many of the Pharisees and Sadducees were coming to be baptized by him, he said to them: "O children of vipers, who has warned you to flee from the coming wrath?"
Make a tree that proves your repentance.
And do not boast when you say: "Ibrahim is our father." For I say to you that Allah is capable of creating children for Ibrahim from these stones.
Here is the axe placed on the roots of the tree trunks. It will cut down every tree that does not bear good fruit, and it will cast it into the fire.
I am sending you forth in water to proclaim your repentance; but he who comes after me is greater than I am, and I am not worthy to stoop and unlace his sandals. He will send you forth in the Holy Spirit and fire.
He will carry his grains in his hand and cleanse them with his own hand, gathering his grains into the storehouse, and burning the chaff with a fire that never goes out. — The Lordship of Jesus
Then Jesus came from Galilee to the Jordan River, because He wished to be baptized by John.
But John tried to stop him and said: "I need you to come to me, so why are you coming here?"
Then Jesus replied, "Allow this to happen now, for it is proper to complete all that God requires." At that time John permitted him to proceed.
Jesus was baptized in the water. And as he came up from the water, heaven was opened, and he saw the Spirit of God descending like a dove and coming to rest upon him.
A voice came from heaven saying: "You are my beloved's son. I am satisfied with you in every way."
Jesus' experience
And the Spirit led Jesus into the wilderness to test him against Satan.
After Jesus had refrained from eating for forty days and forty nights, he became hungry.
A tested one came to him #The Tested One. 3:4 That is, Satan. And he said to him: "If you are the son of God, say to these stones that they become loaves of bread."
But Jesus answered him, "The Scripture says, 'Man does not live by bread alone, but by every word that comes from the mouth of God.'"
Then Iblis took him to the Holy City and placed him on the summit of the Temple.
He said to him: "If you are truly the Son of God, come down from here yourself. The Book says: 'God commands His angels to take you.' And: 'They will carry you on their hands so that your foot may not touch the stone.'"
And Jesus answered him: "The Book also says: 'The Lord your God will not test you.'"
Then Satan took him to a high mountain and showed before his eyes the kingdoms of the world and their glory.
Then he said to him: "I will give you all of this if you prostrate yourself before me."
Then Jesus said to him, "Get away, Satan! For the Scripture says: 'You shall worship the Lord your God and serve Him only.'"
At that time Satan left him, and angels came to serve him. Jesus begins his ministry in Galilee.
And when Jesus heard that John had been imprisoned, he returned to Galilee.
But he did not stay in Nablus, rather he went and settled in the city of Kfar Nahum, near the Sea of Galilee, in the regions of Zebulun and Naphthalim.
This happened so that what God said through the prophet Isaiah might be fulfilled:
The land of Zebulun and Naphtali, by the way of the sea, across the river, the land of Galilee, where the strangers dwell.
The people dwelling in darkness saw a great light; those sitting upon the earth of death's shadows saw light.
From that time on, Jesus began to teach and say: "Repent, for the kingdom of heaven has come near." Jesus chose some disciples.
While Jesus was walking along the shore of the Sea of Galilee, He saw two brothers, Simon, who was also called Peter, and Andrew, casting a net into the sea; they were fishermen.
He said to them: "Follow me, and I will make you fishers of men."
Then they closed their windows and followed him.
Then Jesus departed from there and saw two other brothers, Jacob son of Zebedee and his brother John. He saw them in the boat with their father Zebedee repairing the nets for fishing, and called them.
They left the boat and went ashore, following him. Jesus knows and heals.
And Jesus traveled throughout every region of Galilee, teaching people in their synagogues and proclaiming the gospel of the kingdom of God. And He healed every disease and affliction among people.
And news of him spread throughout all parts of Syria, so that they brought to him all the sick with various diseases and pains, the possessed by evil spirits, the epileptics, and the paralyzed, and Jesus healed them.
And large crowds followed him, coming from the Galilean region, from the ten cities, from Jerusalem, from the Judaean region, and from the eastern bank of the Jordan River.
Teaching of Jesus
And when Jesus saw the crowd, he went up onto a hill and sat down. Then his disciples came to him,
And he began to speak and teach them and said:
Blessed are the poor in spirit, for theirs is the kingdom of heaven.
O joy to the believers, for God will strengthen them.
Blessed are the humble, for they shall inherit the earth. #Inherit the earth. 5:5 See Psalm 37:11. Here it may mean a future spiritual inheritance.
Blessed are the hungry and the thirsty for the kingdom of God, #to do God's will. 6:5 Literally: "Blessed are the hungry." Because God will satisfy them.
O joy to the merciful, for Allah will show them mercy.
O believers, rejoice, for they will see God.
Hallelujah to those working for peace, for they are calling the children of God.
Blessed are the persecuted for the sake of righteousness, for the kingdom of heaven is theirs.
"Blessed are you when people insult you and persecute you, and falsely accuse you of committing evil, because you are righteous."
Rejoice and be glad, for your rewards will be great in heaven. For they treated the prophets who lived before you in the same way. Salt and light
"You are salt for all people. But if salt loses its flavor, what do we do with it to make it good again? It is no longer fit for anything except to be cast outside the house, where feet may tread upon it."
"You are the light of the world. It is impossible to hide a city built on a mountain,"
People do not light a lamp and place it under a vessel! Rather, they place it on a stand so that it can illuminate everyone in the house.
In this way also, let your light shine before men, that they may see your good works and praise your Father in heaven." Jesus and the Law of Moses
Do not think that I have come to abolish the law of Moses or the teachings of the prophets. I have not come to abolish them, but to fulfill them.
I tell you the truth: until the heavens and the earth disappear, not a single letter or dot of the Law will vanish, until everything written in it is fulfilled.
Therefore, he who breaks the smallest of these commandments and teaches people to do the same will be considered the least in the kingdom of heaven. But he who observes these commandments and teaches others to observe them will be considered the greatest in the kingdom of heaven.
For I tell you that unless you increase your obedience to God over the obedience of the scholars of the law and the Pharisees, you will not enter the kingdom of heaven. Anger
You know that it was said to your fathers: "Do not kill. #Do not kill. 21:5 From the Book of Exodus 20:13 and the Book of Deuteronomy 5:17. Whoever kills deserves judgment."
As for me, I say to you that whoever is angry with another person deserves to be tried, and whoever insults another person should stand before the judicial council. And anyone who says to another person, "You fool!" deserves hell.
Therefore, if you are offering a sacrifice at the altar, and then you remember that someone else has something against you,
Leave your offering there in front of the altar, go and first make peace with that person, then return and present your offering.
Salem, get rid of him quickly as you walk with him to court. Otherwise, he will hand you over to the judge, and the judge will hand you over to the jailer, who will send you to prison.
I tell you the truth, you will not leave until the last of your sins is sealed. Adultery
"We heard that it was said: 'Do not weigh.' #Do not weigh. 27:5 From the Book of Exodus 20:14, and the Book of Deuteronomy 5:18."
As for me, I say to you: whoever looks at a woman with lust has already committed adultery with her in his heart.
Therefore, if your right eye causes you to commit sin, pluck it out and cast it far from you. It is better to lose one member of your body than to have your entire body cast into hell.
And if your right hand causes you to sin, cut it off and cast it far from you. It is better to lose one member of your body than to have your entire body cast into hell. Divorce
It was also said: "If a man divorces his wife, let him give her a document to prove it." #If a man divorces ... that. 31:5 From the Book of Deuteronomy 24:1.
As for me, I say to you that whoever divorces his wife except for immorality, does so to lead her into immorality. And whoever marries a divorced woman commits adultery. Oath.
"We heard that it was also said to your fathers: 'Do not swear by falsehood, but fulfill what you have sworn to do for the Lord.' #Do not make vows... for the Lord. 33:5 See Leviticus 19:12, Numbers 30:2, and Deuteronomy 23:21."
As for me, I say to you: never swear at all.
Do not swear by the heavens, for they are Allah's throne, nor by the earth, for it is beneath his feet, #beneath his feet. 35:5 meaning "under his authority." Nor by the city of Jerusalem, for it is the city of the Great King.
Do not claim your hair, because you cannot make a strand of it black or white.
Say, "Yes," if you intend to say "Yes," and say, "No," if you intend to say "No." All that goes beyond this is evil. #Evil. 37:5 The Devil. Resistance to evil
"We heard that it was said: 'An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth.' #An eye... for a tooth. 38:5 from the Book of Exodus 21:24, and the Book of Leviticus 24:20."
As for me, I say: do not resist evil. But if someone strikes you on your right cheek, turn to him the left also.
And if anyone wants to accuse you to take your shirt, let him also take your coat.
And if anyone compels you to walk with him one mile, walk with him two miles.
And if anyone asks you for something, give it to him. Do not refuse to lend to anyone who asks you for a loan. Love for all.
"We heard that it was said: 'Love your friend, and hate your enemy.' #Love... your enemy. 43:5 From the book of Leviticus 19:18."
As for me, I say to you: Love your enemies and pray for those who persecute you.
Thus you will become children of your father who is in heaven. For God causes the sun to rise upon the sinners and the righteous, and sends rain upon the pious and the wicked.
If you only love those who love you, what reward do you deserve? Shouldn't tax collectors do the same?
And if you only cherish your brothers, what sets you apart from others? Do they not also commit such acts as worshipping idols?
Therefore, be complete as your heavenly Father is complete.
The gift
"Be careful not to give your alms in front of people expecting them to be praised; otherwise, your Father in heaven will not reward you."
When you give to the needy, do not announce it as if you were blowing a horn like the hypocrites do in gatherings and streets, seeking people's praise. I tell you the truth, they have received their full reward for that.
But when giving to the needy, do not let your left hand know what your right hand does.
So that your offering may be made in secret. And your father, who sees what happens in secret, will reward you. Prayer
"And when you pray, do not be like the hypocrites, for they love to pray in assemblies and corners of streets so that people may see them. I tell you the truth, they have already received their full reward for that."
But when you pray, go into your room and close the door, and pray to your father in secret. And your father who sees what happens in secret will reward you.
And when you pray, do not recite words without understanding, as do the worshippers of idols, who think that their prayers will be accepted because of the volume of their speech.
Therefore, do not be like them, because your fathers know what you need even before you ask them for it.
Therefore, pray as follows: "Our Father who is in heaven, hallowed be your name,"
Let your kingdom come, and let your will be done, on earth as it is in heaven.
Today we were given bread to fill our day.
And forgive us our sins, as we forgive those who sin against us.
Do not let us enter into trial, but deliver us from the evil one. #TheEvilOne. 13:6 The Devil (Iblis). For you have the kingdom and power and glory, forever and ever. Amen.
For if you forgive the people's sins, your heavenly father will also forgive you.
But if you do not forgive others their sins, neither will your father forgive your sins. Fasting
"And when you fast, do not become like the hypocrites who display sorrow on their faces. Indeed, they change their countenances so that people will clearly see that they are fasting. I tell you the truth, they have already received their full reward."
But when you fast, put oil on your head and wash your face.
So that people won't notice you are fasting. Your father, whom you don't see, will see this. Then your father, who sees what happens in secret, will reward you. God, not money.
Do not store your treasures on earth, where rust and mold will destroy them, and where thieves may break in and steal them.
But store up for yourselves treasures in heaven, where neither rust nor corrosion spoils them, nor can thieves enter to steal them.
Because your heart will be where your treasure is.
"The soul of the body is the eye. If your eyes are pure, then your entire body will be filled with light."
But if your eyes are evil, your body will also be filled with darkness. If the light within you is truly darkness, how can the darkness within you be any different?
No one can serve two masters. Either he will hate one and love the other, or he will hold fast to one and despise the other. You cannot serve God and wealth. #Wealth. 24:6 Literally, "Mamonah." This is an Aramaic word meaning "wealth," in its negative sense, representing here a god people serve instead of God. The kingdom of God comes first.
Therefore I say to you, do not worry about your livelihood, that is, about what you will eat or drink. Nor do not worry about your body, that is, about what you will wear. For life is more important than food, and the body is more important than clothing.
Look at the birds; they do not sow or reap, nor do they store grain in granaries, yet your Lord provides for them. Are you not far more valuable in the sight of God than the birds?
Who among you can add a minute to his life when he worries?
"And why are you worried about what you will wear? Look at how field flowers grow. They don't tire nor do they spin."
But I say to you, not even one of them has been like one of them, nor even Solomon in all his glory.
If Allah were to wear the grass of the fields that you see here today and throw it into the oven tomorrow, would He not care for you more than that, O people of little faith?
Therefore, do not be worried nor ask yourselves: "What shall we eat?" or "What shall we drink?" or "What shall we wear?"
These are things others in the world are striving for, and your heavenly father knows that you need all of them.
But attend first to the kingdom of God and to righteousness, and all these things will also be given to you.
Do not worry about tomorrow, for each day has enough worries of its own, and tomorrow will have its own concerns.
Judging others
Do not judge others, lest God judge you.
For he will judge you according to the way you judge others. And as you measure out to others, so will others measure out to you.
"Why do you see the straw in your brother's eye, but do not notice the large piece of wood in your own eye?"
How can you tell your friend: "Let me pull out the straw from your eye, and there's a large piece of wood in your eye?"
O hypocrite! First remove the plank from your own eye, and then you will be able to clearly see how to remove the speck from your brother's eye.
"Do not give what is sacred to dogs, nor throw your treasures in front of pigs! Pigs will trample them with their feet, and dogs will turn to you and tear you apart. Persist in your demand"
Ask and it will be given to you, seek and you will find, knock and the door will be opened for you.
For whoever asks shall receive, and whoever seeks shall find, and to whoever knocks, the door shall be opened for him.
Of you, if a son asks for a loaf of bread, will you give him a stone?
Or if he asks for a fish, will you give him one?
You, despite your own shortcomings, know how to give your children good gifts. Isn't the Father in heaven much more qualified to give good gifts to those who ask Him? The Golden Rule
"Treat others as you would like to be treated. This is the essence of Moses' law and the teachings of the prophets. The path of heaven and the path of hell."
"Enter through the narrow gate that leads to heaven, for the gate leading to destruction is wide, and the road to it is easy, and many enter it."
The gate leading to life is very narrow, and the path to it is full of difficulties; only a few find this way. Warning against false teachings
Beware of the false prophets who come to you in the form of mythical beasts and fables, but within them are fierce wolves.
You will know them by their deeds. No one gathers grapes from thorns, or figs from thistles!
Similarly, every healthy tree bears a healthy fruit, and every unhealthy tree bears an unhealthy fruit.
A healthy tree cannot produce a bad fruit, nor can a bad tree produce good fruit.
And every tree that does not bear good fruit will be cut down and thrown into the fire.
Thus, you will know the false prophets by their fruits.
Not everyone who says to me, 'Lord, Lord,' will enter the kingdom of heaven, but only those who do the will of my Father who is in heaven.
Many will say to me on that last day: "O Lord, O Lord, did we not prophesy in Your name? Did we not drive out evil spirits in Your name? Did we not perform many miracles in Your name?"
At that time I will say to them plainly: I have never known you. Depart from me, you doers of evil. The wise man and the fool
"Everyone who listens to my teachings and puts them into practice is like a wise man who builds his house on rock."
Rain fell, floods rose, the wind blew and struck that house, but it did not collapse, because its foundation was on rock.
And whoever hears my words and does not put them into practice is like a foolish man who builds his house on sand.
Then it rained, the floodwaters rose, the wind blew and struck that house, and it collapsed in a terrible fall!
And when Jesus finished this teaching, the people were amazed at his teaching.
Because he taught them by authority, not like my teachers of the law.
Jesus heals the leper
Then Jesus descended from the mountain, and many followed him.
A man came to him, prostrated before him, and said: "O Lord, you are able to make me pure, if you wish."
And Jesus stretched out His hand and touched him, and said, "I will; be made clean." And immediately he was cleansed.
Then Jesus said to him, "Do not tell anyone what happened to you, but go and present yourself to the priest, #go... to the priest. 4:8 The priest was the one who, according to the Law, decided when leprosy was considered clean. He will present the offering Moses commanded, so that people will know you have been healed." Roman officer of faith
And Jesus entered the city of Capernaum, and a Roman officer came to him. #Roman officer. 5:8 Literally "commander of a hundred." Repeated in the numbers 8, 13.
He said: "O master, my servant is very ill and lying in bed at home. He is motionless and suffering from severe pain."
Then Jesus said to him, "I will go and heal him."
Then the officer replied: "O sir, I do not deserve for you to enter my home; all you need to do is say a word and my servant will be healed."
And I myself am a man under authority, and I have soldiers who act according to my commands. I tell one soldier: "Go!" and he goes. I tell another: "Come!" and he comes. I tell my servant: "Do this!" and he does it.
When Jesus heard this, he was amazed and said to those who were following him: "Truly I tell you, I have never found such faith even among the children of Israel."
I tell you that many will come from the east and west, and will sit down with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob in the kingdom of heaven.
As for those who were meant to inherit the kingdom, they will go into darkness outside. There, people will weep and gnash their teeth!
Then Jesus said to the officer, "Go, and let it be as you believed." At that very moment the officer's servant was healed. "Bear our diseases"
And when Jesus came to Peter's house, he saw Peter's wife lying on the bed, with a high fever.
And Jesus took her hand, and the fever left her; she rose and began to serve him.
That evening, people brought to him many individuals possessed by evil spirits; he expelled the spirits at his command, and healed all the sick.
This happened so that what God said through the Prophet Isaiah might be fulfilled: "He took our infirmities and bore our diseases." – Jesus
And seeing a large crowd around Him, Jesus commanded His disciples to go across the lake to the other side.
A student of his jurisprudence came to him and said to him: "O teacher, I will follow you wherever you go."
Then Jesus said to him, "The foxes have their dens, and the birds of the sky their nests, but the Son of Man has nowhere to lay his head."
Another of his disciples said to him: "O Lord, allow me to wait until I bury my father."
But Jesus said to him, "Follow me, and let the dead bury their dead." Jesus calms the storm
And Jesus took the boat and entered it, and his disciples followed him.
Then a violent storm arose in the lake, and the boat was being swallowed by the waves. Jesus was asleep.
They approached him and woke him up, saying: "O Lord, we have reached our limit; indeed, we are drowning."
Then Jesus said to them, "Why are you afraid, you of little faith?" And he got up and commanded the wind and the sea; and there was an overwhelming silence.
But they were amazed and said, "What kind of man is this? Even the winds and the sea obey him!" Jesus casts out demons from two men.
Then Jesus went to the region of the Gerasenes, on the other side of the lake. Two men from the tombs came to Him, possessed by unclean spirits. The two men were dangerous, so no one dared to pass that way.
The evil spirits screamed: "What do you want from us, son of God? Have you come here to torture us before the designated time?"
There was a large herd of pigs being herded at a distance from them.
The evil spirits approached him and said: "If you expel us, we will send ourselves to the pig herd."
Then Jesus said to them, "Go!" And the unclean spirits left the two men and entered the pigs. At that moment, the entire herd rushed down from the hilltop into the lake, and the pigs sank into the water.
The shepherds fled to the town and told the people what had happened to the possessed people with evil spirits.
All the people of the town came out to see Jesus. When they saw him, they asked him to leave their area.
Jesus heals a paralytic
Then Jesus got into a boat and crossed to the other side of the lake; and he arrived at his town.
So some people brought to him a paralyzed man lying on his bed. When Jesus saw their faith, he said to the paralytic, "Son, your sins are forgiven."
Some of my Sharia scholars say: "This man disrespects God with his words."
Jesus knew what they were thinking, and said to them: "Why do evil thoughts dwell in your hearts?"
Which is easier: to say "your sins are forgiven," or to say "get up and walk"?
But I will show you that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive sins. And He said to the paralytic man, "Arise, take up your mat and go to your house!"
He rose and went to his house.
And when people saw this, they were filled with fear, and they praised God for having given such power to people. When will Jesus follow?
While Jesus was walking, he saw a man named Matthew sitting at a tax collector's booth. Jesus said to him, "Follow me," and he got up and followed him.
While Jesus was eating in the house of Matthew, many tax collectors and sinners came and ate with him and his disciples.
When the Pharisees saw this, they asked his disciples, "Why does your teacher eat with tax collectors and sinners?"
When Jesus heard this, he said: "The healthy do not need a physician, but the sick."
