Jesus, with him Moses and Elijah
After six days, Jesus took Peter, James, and John his brother, and led them up a high mountain where they were alone.
While they were there, Jesus' appearance changed and he shone like the sun; his clothes became white as light.
And suddenly Moses and Elijah appeared before the disciples, and they were talking with Jesus.
Peter said to Jesus: "Lord, how beautiful it is to be here! If you wish, let us set up three tabernacles here—one for you, one for Moses, and one for Elijah."
While Peter was speaking, a bright cloud overshadowed them, and a voice came from it saying: "This is my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased. Listen to him."
When the students heard this, they were terrified and fell to the ground on their faces.
Jesus approached them and touched them, saying, "Rise up, do not be afraid."
And when they looked around them, they saw no one but Jesus.
As they were descending from the mountain, Jesus warned them and said: "Do not tell anyone what you have seen, until the Son of Man rises from the dead."
